'''Hubbard College of Administration International''' is an [[School accreditation|unaccredited]]<ref>"Apart from the Hubbard College of Administration International, an unaccredited post-secondary school, only students taught in a number..."{{cite web | first = Anil | last = Dawar | title =Will Smith funds school teaching Scientology creator's study method | url =https://www.theguardian.com/world/2008/may/19/usa.filmnews | work = | publisher = [[The Guardian]] | date = 19 May 2008 | accessdate = 2009-03-14}}</ref> school that teaches administration using methods developed by [[Church of Scientology]] founder, [[L. Ron Hubbard]].<ref>{{cite web | first = Jeff | last = Walsh | title = A broader look at the organization | work = Inside the Church of Scientology | publisher = [[Boston Herald]] |url = https://www.apologeticsindex.org/Sciorg.pdf | date = 1998-03-01 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | first = Michelle V. | last = Rafter | title = EarthLink Connects | url = http://www.thestandard.com/article/0,1902,436,00.html | work = | publisher = [[The Industry Standard]] | date = 1998-05-28 | accessdate = 2007-10-04 }}{{Dead link|date=November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Lawsuit: Firm's training was front for Scientology |url=http://www.dailysouthtown.com/business/433823,dst_bti_619.article |work=Business |publisher=[[Daily Southtown]] |date=2007-06-19 |accessdate=2007-10-04 |df= }}{{dead link|date=May 2017|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | first = Dominic | last = Kennedy | title = &#8216;Church&#8217; that yearns for respectability | url = https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/church-that-yearns-for-respectability-rps7nzwbqrn | work = | publisher = [[The Times]] | date = 2007-06-23 | accessdate = 2007-10-04 | location=London}}</ref> The headquarters for the school is located at 320 North Vermont Avenue, [[Los Angeles, California]] 90004. The school began operations in 1990 and its current headquarters were established in 2001.{{Citation needed|date=February 2009}} It is a [[501(c)(3)]] public charity, and as a religious organization does not file an annual return,<ref>{{cite web | title = GuideStar - HUBBARD COLLEGE OF ADMINISTRATION: | publisher = Philanthropic Research, Inc. | url = http://www.guidestar.org/pqShowGsReport.do?partner=guidestar&npoId=58116 | accessdate = 2007-06-22 }}{{Dead link|date=November 2018}}</ref> however it states itself to be a "secular educational institution".<ref>{{cite web|title=FAQs - About L. Ron Hubbard |publisher=Hubbard College of Administration International |url=http://www.hubbardcollege.org/faqs/faqs_aboutlrh.html |accessdate=2007-06-22 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070618075908/http://www.hubbardcollege.org/faqs/faqs_aboutlrh.html |archivedate=2007-06-18 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
== Admission requirements == Students are not required to have a [[high school]] diploma to gain early admission and start taking courses at the school. Students are not required to take the [[ACT (examination)|ACT]] or [[SAT]] tests to gain admission. The school does have an application form that must be completed and submitted with a $150 fee. The school requests letters of recommendation and says it tests students for IQ, leadership qualities, and reading level. The admission process may also include interviews to determine an applicant's qualifications and desire to further his/her education.
== Programs offered == The school grants a "Specialized Associate Degree Program" which it calls, "Associate of Applied Science Degree of Management and Administration". The school also offers "Continuing Education Certificate Programs". There also exist a number of "Public Workshops and Corporate Programs" which are short courses on specific topics. The school also provides [[World Institute of Scientology Enterprises|WISE]] certificate programs; WISE being a Scientology-affiliated business group.<ref>[http://www.scientology.org/en_US/world/news/wise/index.html Enabling Groups to Flourish and Prosper] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080704133824/http://www.scientology.org/en_US/world/news/wise/index.html |date=2008-07-04 }}</ref>
Hubbard College of Administration Is now in the process of being accredited.{{Citation needed|date=May 2017}}
== Cost == As of October, 2006, the tuition for the "degree program" costs $30,179; books and supplies cost $2,643.28; the total cost is $32,852.28. Costs for the continuing education programs range from ~$3000 to ~$18,000. Costs of public workshops and corporate programs are ~$250. WISE certificate programs range from ~$6000 to $8000.{{Citation needed|date=February 2009}}
The school's website says that financial aid is available, however, since the school is not accredited, students are not eligible to participate in any federally-funded financial aid programs, such as [[Pell Grant]]s, [[Perkins Loan]]s, or any other government assisted loan programs.
As of January, 2015, the tuition for the "degree program" costs $52,000–books and supplies excluded.
== Teaching == The school teaches a method of business administration developed by L. Ron Hubbard. The school uses a teaching method called "[[Study Tech]]nology", also developed by Hubbard, as a method of teaching its students. The school does not have semesters or terms. Students can begin taking courses at any time of the year and they may attend either full-time or part-time.{{Citation needed|date=February 2009}}
