A '''UFO convention''' is a [[convention (meeting)|convention]] about [[Unidentified flying object|UFO]]s that usually take place annually at [[hotel]]s or [[convention center]]s. Historically, many would mainly feature [[contactee]]s giving presentations about their experiences. Other topics, like [[UFO conspiracy theory]], general [[conspiracy theory]], and other [[paranormal]] phenomena are often discussed. However, some serious topical discussions and seminars are conducted at modern conventions{{Citation needed|date=June 2017}}.
* ''[[Giant Rock]] Spacecraft Conventions'', held by [[George Van Tassel]] and helped pay for the [[Integratron]] from the mid-1950s to the mid-1970s near [[Landers, California]]<ref>[http://www.forteantimes.com/articles/118_rock.shtml ''The Giant Rock Conventions''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070405091500/http://www.forteantimes.com/articles/118_rock.shtml |date=2007-04-05 }}, Gregory Bishop and Kenn Thomas, [[Fortean Times]], January 1999</ref> * ''[[Mutual UFO Network|MUFON]] International UFO Symposium'' (1969-present)<ref>[http://www.mufon.com/who-we-are.html, The [[Mutual UFO Network]] "Who We Are" page]</ref> * ''[[National UFO Conference]]'' (1999-present) * ''[[Conspiracy Con]]'', produced by [[Brian William Hall]] from 2001-present
UFO conventions have been featured in various [[pop culture]]:
'''Television''' * [[The Lone Gunmen]], from the 1994 ''X-Files'' episode ''[[E.B.E. (The X-Files)|E.B.E.]]'', originate from a UFO convention * ''[[Esteemsters]]'', 1997 ''Daria'' episode * ''The Convention'', 2000 ''[[Roswell (TV series)|Roswell]]'' episode * ''[[Attack of the Saucer Morons]]'', 2001 ''Invader Zim'' episode * ''Alien Abductions'', 2003 ''[[Penn & Teller: Bullshit!|Bullshit!]]'' episode, features 3 days at a UFO convention
